San Lucas first appeared as a [[census designated place]] in the [[2000 U.S. census]].<ref name=2000CensusCA/>

===2020===
The [[2020 United States census]] reported that San Lucas had a population of 324. The population density was {{convert|822.3|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. The racial makeup of San Lucas was 139 (42.9%) [[White Americans|White]], 1 (0.3%) [[African Americans|African American]], 3 (0.9%) [[Native Americans in the United States|Native American]], 1 (0.3%) [[Asian Americans|Asian]], 2 (0.6%) [[Pacific Islander Americans|Pacific Islander]], 137 (42.3%) from [[Race (United States Census)|other races]], and 41 (12.7%) from two or more races. [[Hispanic and Latino Americans|Hispanic or Latino]] of any race were 302 persons (93.2%).<ref name=DP1>{{cite web |title=San Lucas CDP, California; DP1: Profile of General Population and Housing Characteristics - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDP2020.DP1?g=1600000US0668140 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=June 3, 2025}}</ref>

The whole population lived in households. There were 76 households, out of which 39 (51.3%) had children under the age of 18 living in them, 45 (59.2%) were married-couple households, 10 (13.2%) were [[cohabitation|cohabiting]] couple households, 14 (18.4%) had a female householder with no partner present, and 7 (9.2%) had a male householder with no partner present. 8 households (10.5%) were one person, and 2 (2.6%) were one person aged 65 or older. The average household size was 4.26.<ref name=DP1/> There were 67 [[family (U.S. Census)|families]] (88.2% of all households).<ref>{{cite web |title=San Lucas CDP, California; P16: Household Type - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDHC2020.P16?g=1600000US0668140 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=June 3, 2025}}</ref>

The age distribution was 112 people (34.6%) under the age of 18, 31 people (9.6%) aged 18 to 24, 92 people (28.4%) aged 25 to 44, 60 people (18.5%) aged 45 to 64, and 29 people (9.0%) who were 65{{nbsp}}years of age or older. The median age was 28.8{{nbsp}}years. For every 100 females, there were 100.0 males.<ref name=DP1/>

There were 76 housing units at an average density of {{convert|192.9|/mi2|/km2|disp=preunit|units&nbsp;|units|}}, which were all occupied, 27 (35.5%) by homeowners and 49 (64.5%) by renters.<ref name=DP1/>

===2010===
The [[2010 United States census]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.census.gov/2010census/popmap/ipmtext.php?fl=06:0668140|archive-url=https://archive.today/20140715032916/http://www.census.gov/2010census/popmap/ipmtext.php?fl=06:0668140|url-status=dead|archive-date=July 15, 2014|title=2010 Census Interactive Population Search: CA - San Lucas CDP|publisher=U.S. Census Bureau|access-date=July 12, 2014}}</ref> reported that San Lucas had a population of 269. The population density was {{convert|682.5|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. The racial makeup of San Lucas was 113 (42.0%) [[White (U.S. Census)|White]], 0 (0.0%) [[African American (U.S. Census)|African American]], 4 (1.5%) [[Native American (U.S. Census)|Native American]], 6 (2.2%) [[Asian (U.S. Census)|Asian]], 0 (0.0%) [[Pacific Islander (U.S. Census)|Pacific Islander]], 127 (47.2%) from [[Race (United States Census)|other races]], and 19 (7.1%) from two or more races. [[Hispanic (U.S. Census)|Hispanic]] or [[Latino (U.S. Census)|Latino]] of any race were 224 persons (83.3%).

The Census reported that 269 people (100% of the population) lived in households, 0 (0%) lived in non-institutionalized group quarters, and 0 (0%) were institutionalized.

There were 67 households, out of which 38 (56.7%) had children under the age of 18 living in them, 46 (68.7%) were [[marriage|opposite-sex married couples]] living together, 8 (11.9%) had a female householder with no husband present, 3 (4.5%) had a male householder with no wife present.  There were 4 (6.0%) [[POSSLQ|unmarried opposite-sex partnerships]], and 0 (0%) [[same-sex partnerships|same-sex married couples or partnerships]]. 7 households (10.4%) were made up of individuals, and 2 (3.0%) had someone living alone who was 65 years of age or older. The average household size was 4.01.  There were 57 [[family (U.S. Census)|families]] (85.1% of all households); the average family size was 4.23.

The population was spread out, with 87 people (32.3%) under the age of 18, 38 people (14.1%) aged 18 to 24, 74 people (27.5%) aged 25 to 44, 58 people (21.6%) aged 45 to 64, and 12 people (4.5%) who were 65 years of age or older.  The median age was 26.3 years. For every 100 females, there were 110.2 males.  For every 100 females age 18 and over, there were 111.6 males.

There were 76 housing units at an average density of {{convert|192.8|/sqmi|/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}, of which 36 (53.7%) were owner-occupied, and 31 (46.3%) were occupied by renters. The homeowner vacancy rate was 0%; the rental vacancy rate was 11.4%.  132 people (49.1% of the population) lived in owner-occupied housing units and 137 people (50.9%) lived in rental housing units.

===2000===
As of the [[census]]<ref name="GR2">{{cite web|url=https://www.census.gov|publisher=[[United States Census Bureau]]|access-date=2008-01-31|title=U.S. Census website}}</ref> of 2000, the median income for a household in the CDP was $31,538, and the median income for a family was $30,536. Males had a median income of $27,000 versus $24,375 for females. The [[per capita income]] for the CDP was $7,834.  About 23.3% of families and 29.7% of the population were below the [[poverty line]], including 38.2% of those under age 18 and 11.4% of those age 65 or over.

